1
00:00:51,680 --> 00:00:52,800
I told you.

2
00:00:53,000 --> 00:00:54,840
The victim didn't die in the rickshaw.

3
00:00:54,840 --> 00:00:56,840
So Dali isn't the killer.

4
00:00:57,280 --> 00:00:59,480
We'll talk about moving the body later.

5
00:00:59,680 --> 00:01:02,140
The priority now is identifying the victim.

6
00:01:08,640 --> 00:01:10,920
I find another place suspicious.

7
00:01:11,400 --> 00:01:11,960
Where?

8
00:01:12,520 --> 00:01:13,520
Jiangjun Temple.

9
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:15,480
Earlier in the rickshaw,

10
00:01:15,640 --> 00:01:17,039
I found some incense ash.

11
00:01:17,360 --> 00:01:18,560
I wasn't sure

12
00:01:18,720 --> 00:01:20,880
if Dali picked it up while working,

13
00:01:21,240 --> 00:01:22,080
or if

14
00:01:22,160 --> 00:01:23,620
the passenger brought it.

15
00:01:24,520 --> 00:01:25,980
Just now on these clothes,

16
00:01:26,080 --> 00:01:27,560
I smelled incense ash too.

17
00:01:33,280 --> 00:01:34,520
For real?

18
00:01:35,080 --> 00:01:36,479
How come I can't smell it?

19
00:01:36,680 --> 00:01:37,120
You...

20
00:01:42,240 --> 00:01:43,570
It's actually not dust,

21
00:01:43,600 --> 00:01:44,530
but incense ash.

22
00:01:45,600 --> 00:01:47,680
Look at the style and material of these clothes.

23
00:01:47,680 --> 00:01:49,720
He looks like a worker for a wealthy family.

24
00:01:49,720 --> 00:01:50,920
He should be a butler.

25
00:01:51,240 --> 00:01:53,920
I, Shencheng's top little diviner, never lie.

26
00:01:54,120 --> 00:01:55,360
My nose is a compass.

27
00:01:56,000 --> 00:01:57,759
So you're the new police dog

28
00:01:57,920 --> 00:01:59,360
at our station.

29
00:01:59,880 --> 00:02:00,680
Peh, peh, peh!

30
00:02:00,760 --> 00:02:02,080
I'm not a dog.

31
00:02:02,320 --> 00:02:03,000
Her?

32
00:02:03,480 --> 00:02:05,010
A leash can't hold her back.

33
00:02:05,120 --> 00:02:05,760
Didi,

34
00:02:06,080 --> 00:02:07,400
we've been working hard for so long.

35
00:02:07,400 --> 00:02:08,479
Take us out for a late-night snack.

36
00:02:08,479 --> 00:02:10,360
- Let's go.
- Give me a break.

37
00:02:11,080 --> 00:02:12,720
I finally found a case.

38
00:02:13,480 --> 00:02:15,280
I must get to the bottom of it.

39
00:02:16,360 --> 00:02:19,000
The victim looks very different from when he was alive.

40
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:20,920
I think right now you need a sketch artist

41
00:02:20,920 --> 00:02:22,720
who can restore his appearance.

42
00:02:23,240 --> 00:02:23,680
Right.

43
00:02:24,560 --> 00:02:26,160
Then we can take the portrait

44
00:02:26,320 --> 00:02:28,720
and identify the person near the Zheng residence.

45
00:02:28,720 --> 00:02:30,160
Then hurry and find Yu Laosi.

46
00:02:30,160 --> 00:02:31,280
Ask him to help draw it.

47
00:02:31,280 --> 00:02:32,160
Old Yu?

48
00:02:33,200 --> 00:02:34,840
He's hard of hearing and has dim eyesight.

49
00:02:34,840 --> 00:02:37,300
No one recognizes his drawings but himself.

50
00:02:41,800 --> 00:02:43,930
I actually have a suitable candidate.

51
00:02:46,360 --> 00:02:47,040
In order to

52
00:02:47,360 --> 00:02:48,240
get home early,

53
00:02:48,680 --> 00:02:49,810
I just kept running.

54
00:02:50,040 --> 00:02:51,480
I ran home for my life.

55
00:02:52,360 --> 00:02:54,200
Captain, the autopsy results are in.

56
00:02:54,200 --> 00:02:55,600
He didn't die last night.

57
00:02:55,760 --> 00:02:56,880
It has nothing to do with Man Dali.

58
00:02:56,880 --> 00:02:57,940
We can release him.

59
00:02:58,160 --> 00:02:58,680
No.

60
00:02:59,320 --> 00:03:01,320
Even if he wasn't killed yesterday,

61
00:03:01,520 --> 00:03:03,160
there's no guarantee he didn't kill him before that.

62
00:03:03,160 --> 00:03:05,040
But he has absolutely no motive.

63
00:03:05,240 --> 00:03:05,840
Besides,

64
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:07,960
what murderer comes to report the case himself?

65
00:03:07,960 --> 00:03:08,480
True.

66
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:11,480
That's because he wanted to move the body last night.

67
00:03:11,480 --> 00:03:12,940
We caught him red-handed.

68
00:03:13,720 --> 00:03:14,800
In a panic,

69
00:03:14,920 --> 00:03:16,840
he lied about a living passenger

70
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:18,880
turning into a white-haired bloody corpse.

71
00:03:18,880 --> 00:03:19,410
Captain.

72
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:23,000
As long as we find the victim's identity and timeline,

73
00:03:23,200 --> 00:03:24,160
won't that prove

74
00:03:24,520 --> 00:03:26,240
if Man Dali is lying?

75
00:03:27,640 --> 00:03:28,170
Correct.

76
00:03:29,400 --> 00:03:31,400
If it's really as Coroner Yang said,

77
00:03:31,400 --> 00:03:32,840
and the man has been dead for two days,

78
00:03:32,840 --> 00:03:34,560
we just need to prove Man Dali had no contact

79
00:03:34,560 --> 00:03:36,490
with the victim before last night.

80
00:03:39,640 --> 00:03:41,640
The sketch artist I invited is here.

81
00:03:44,520 --> 00:03:45,120
Landlady.

82
00:03:45,520 --> 00:03:46,160
Wu Yue.

83
00:03:46,360 --> 00:03:47,840
Is my wife okay?

84
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:49,400
Is she doing fine at home?

85
00:03:54,400 --> 00:03:54,840
Here.

86
00:03:55,600 --> 00:03:57,280
Juan is at home waiting for you.

87
00:03:57,280 --> 00:03:58,010
Don't worry.

88
00:03:58,200 --> 00:03:59,730
We'll take good care of her.

89
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:00,840
Thank you.

90
00:04:00,920 --> 00:04:02,180
We are here to help you.

91
00:04:02,680 --> 00:04:03,280
Landlady.

92
00:04:03,520 --> 00:04:04,880
I'm really innocent.

93
00:04:05,440 --> 00:04:05,970
Man Dali.

94
00:04:06,360 --> 00:04:07,240
Describe the person on the bus,

95
00:04:07,240 --> 00:04:08,240
what he looked like when he was alive,

96
00:04:08,240 --> 00:04:09,320
to Weiqing.

97
00:04:09,640 --> 00:04:11,240
Don't leave out a single detail.

98
00:04:11,240 --> 00:04:12,570
Only by identifying him

99
00:04:12,600 --> 00:04:13,860
can we clear your name.

100
00:04:14,080 --> 00:04:14,560
Okay.

101
00:04:15,320 --> 00:04:16,000
I remember,

102
00:04:16,680 --> 00:04:18,640
he seemed to be in his forties.

103
00:04:19,160 --> 00:04:20,760
And his height...

104
00:04:20,959 --> 00:04:22,640
he was about as tall as me.

105
00:04:23,840 --> 00:04:24,970
He was wearing a hat.

106
00:04:41,400 --> 00:04:42,460
Is this the person?

107
00:04:43,720 --> 00:04:44,080
Yes.

108
00:04:44,440 --> 00:04:44,880
Yes, exactly.

109
00:04:44,880 --> 00:04:46,400
That's about what he looked like.

110
00:04:46,400 --> 00:04:48,000
The landlady drew a great likeness.

111
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:49,400
It really is the same man

112
00:04:49,400 --> 00:04:50,480
we saw last night.

113
00:04:51,640 --> 00:04:53,500
Your drawing skills are amazing.

114
00:04:53,880 --> 00:04:55,159
He looks a lot like the deceased,

115
00:04:55,159 --> 00:04:56,760
except his hair isn't white.

116
00:04:57,360 --> 00:04:59,520
But how could someone who's been dead for nearly three days

117
00:04:59,520 --> 00:05:01,080
hail a rickshaw?

118
00:05:01,360 --> 00:05:01,960
Right now,

119
00:05:02,600 --> 00:05:04,360
this drawing is our only clue.

120
00:05:05,040 --> 00:05:06,040
As for the rest...

121
00:05:17,280 --> 00:05:18,480
This smell.

122
00:05:20,120 --> 00:05:20,920
This smell...

123
00:05:20,920 --> 00:05:23,250
is very similar to the white fog back then.

124
00:05:26,120 --> 00:05:26,920
That's right.

125
00:05:27,720 --> 00:05:29,160
Last night, I also smelled

126
00:05:29,160 --> 00:05:31,220
a strong scent of foreign saltpeter.

127
00:05:31,640 --> 00:05:33,440
No wonder it smells so familiar.

128
00:05:33,800 --> 00:05:35,200
It is magic smoke powder.

129
00:05:35,640 --> 00:05:37,159
Also known as foreign saltpeter.

130
00:05:37,159 --> 00:05:39,420
It produces a lot of white smoke when lit.

131
00:05:39,640 --> 00:05:42,240
It is used to block vision during magic tricks.

132
00:05:42,960 --> 00:05:44,720
This must be a planned

133
00:05:45,400 --> 00:05:46,659
body swapping scheme.

134
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:48,330
So it was premeditated.

135
00:05:49,280 --> 00:05:51,680
But where could they get so much saltpeter?

136
00:05:52,640 --> 00:05:54,500
Ordinary families wouldn't have

137
00:05:54,560 --> 00:05:56,400
saltpeter for making matches.

138
00:05:57,520 --> 00:05:58,450
A match factory.

139
00:05:59,040 --> 00:06:01,440
The Zheng family on Furong Street runs one.

140
00:06:01,800 --> 00:06:03,520
The head of the household is Zheng Jinxian.

141
00:06:03,520 --> 00:06:04,520
The Zheng family.

142
00:06:04,840 --> 00:06:07,440
That person also took the rickshaw from there.

143
00:06:07,600 --> 00:06:08,930
Do you know that family?

144
00:06:09,120 --> 00:06:10,120
I don't know them,

145
00:06:10,280 --> 00:06:12,320
but I've heard my husband mention them.

146
00:06:12,320 --> 00:06:14,320
Half the properties on Furong Street

147
00:06:14,320 --> 00:06:15,850
belong to the Zheng family.

148
00:06:16,520 --> 00:06:19,380
Paying two silver dollars just for a rickshaw ride.

149
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:22,600
This butler is more generous than a Westerner.

150
00:06:23,560 --> 00:06:25,020
This case is complicated.

151
00:06:25,080 --> 00:06:26,760
I'll introduce you to a legal expert.

152
00:06:26,760 --> 00:06:28,160
He should be able to help.

153
00:06:31,360 --> 00:06:32,120
Who are you?

154
00:06:32,280 --> 00:06:33,280
Police business.

155
00:06:33,840 --> 00:06:34,700
You can't go in.

156
00:06:36,800 --> 00:06:37,840
Please cooperate with the investigation.

157
00:06:37,840 --> 00:06:39,400
Ask your master, Zheng Jinxian, to come out.

158
00:06:39,400 --> 00:06:40,659
Our master isn't here.

159
00:06:40,720 --> 00:06:43,080
He went out of town on business three days ago.

160
00:06:43,080 --> 00:06:44,540
Then who is in charge here?

161
00:06:44,720 --> 00:06:46,050
Don't you have a butler?

162
00:06:46,080 --> 00:06:47,540
The Mistress is in charge.

163
00:06:47,560 --> 00:06:47,960
She is

164
00:06:48,280 --> 00:06:49,680
resting in the backyard.

165
00:06:49,720 --> 00:06:51,120
Then ask your Mistress to come out.

166
00:06:51,120 --> 00:06:52,980
I need to ask about Zheng Jinxian.

167
00:06:53,240 --> 00:06:54,360
Are you done yet?

168
00:07:01,160 --> 00:07:02,960
What do you want with our master?

169
00:07:06,440 --> 00:07:07,680
Why is it her?

170
00:07:18,760 --> 00:07:19,480
Master.

171
00:07:20,840 --> 00:07:21,570
Please, sit.

172
00:07:24,600 --> 00:07:28,200
Have you visited a temple recently, Madam?

173
00:07:28,760 --> 00:07:29,520
Yes.

174
00:07:30,520 --> 00:07:32,380
You went to the General's Temple.

175
00:07:54,040 --> 00:07:55,080
Master, this...

176
00:07:58,480 --> 00:08:00,010
There is blood in the water.

177
00:08:00,920 --> 00:08:01,780
This person...

178
00:08:02,040 --> 00:08:03,640
Did not die a peaceful death.

179
00:08:03,800 --> 00:08:04,480
He...

180
00:08:05,360 --> 00:08:07,000
died in a work accident.

181
00:08:10,760 --> 00:08:12,680
That remains to be seen.

182
00:08:16,160 --> 00:08:17,490
Pour the guest some tea.

183
00:08:17,760 --> 00:08:18,820
Hello, Mrs. Zheng.

184
00:08:19,040 --> 00:08:20,570
I don't deserve that title.

185
00:08:20,880 --> 00:08:22,440
The Master had a First Wife.

186
00:08:22,880 --> 00:08:25,140
Only after his original wife passed away

187
00:08:25,240 --> 00:08:27,560
did he dare to take me as a concubine.

188
00:08:28,080 --> 00:08:30,000
You are quite honest.

189
00:08:31,280 --> 00:08:32,960
What is there to hide?

190
00:08:33,520 --> 00:08:35,720
It's not like I wanted to be a concubine.

191
00:08:36,960 --> 00:08:37,640
This man,

192
00:08:39,080 --> 00:08:39,940
do you know him?

193
00:08:40,480 --> 00:08:42,679
He looks like our former butler,

194
00:08:43,640 --> 00:08:44,560
Gu Mancang.

195
00:08:45,440 --> 00:08:46,120
But,

196
00:08:46,560 --> 00:08:48,020
he was fired five days ago.

197
00:08:48,440 --> 00:08:49,640
Why was he fired?

198
00:08:50,080 --> 00:08:50,940
Where did he go?

199
00:08:52,520 --> 00:08:53,780
He had sticky fingers,

200
00:08:54,040 --> 00:08:55,370
so the Master fired him.

201
00:08:55,600 --> 00:08:56,720
Where did he go?

202
00:08:57,000 --> 00:08:57,920
I don't know.

203
00:08:58,640 --> 00:09:00,080
He's not from Shencheng.

204
00:09:00,840 --> 00:09:02,600
Maybe he went back to his hometown.

205
00:09:02,600 --> 00:09:04,400
Last night he hailed a rickshaw.

206
00:09:04,400 --> 00:09:05,920
When he arrived at Jiangjun Temple...

207
00:09:05,920 --> 00:09:08,850
The coachman found him bleeding from every orifice.

208
00:09:12,320 --> 00:09:13,480
Butler Gu is dead.

209
00:09:14,600 --> 00:09:16,130
It never rains but it pours.

210
00:09:16,240 --> 00:09:19,280
Officer Yao didn't say Gu Mancang was dead.

211
00:09:20,120 --> 00:09:22,160
Why do you think he's dead?

212
00:09:24,360 --> 00:09:27,160
Didn't you say he was bleeding from every orifice?

213
00:09:27,560 --> 00:09:29,120
Wouldn't that mean he's dead?

214
00:09:29,120 --> 00:09:30,160
He is indeed dead.

215
00:09:30,600 --> 00:09:33,080
He even turned into a white-haired blood corpse.

216
00:09:33,080 --> 00:09:35,080
We want to know where he was from,

217
00:09:35,920 --> 00:09:37,050
and what he was like.

218
00:09:37,200 --> 00:09:38,400
How would I know?

219
00:09:38,760 --> 00:09:40,560
I just married into this family.

220
00:09:40,760 --> 00:09:41,760
Why don't you wait

221
00:09:41,840 --> 00:09:43,440
for my husband to return

222
00:09:43,640 --> 00:09:44,570
and ask him then?

223
00:09:47,000 --> 00:09:48,040
My stomach hurts.

224
00:09:48,120 --> 00:09:50,040
May I use the restroom, Madam?

225
00:09:51,480 --> 00:09:52,540
Go to the backyard.

226
00:09:52,840 --> 00:09:54,570
It's at the end of the corridor.

227
00:09:55,280 --> 00:09:56,280
Thank you, Madam.

228
00:09:57,520 --> 00:09:58,480
It's coming out.

229
00:10:07,520 --> 00:10:09,720
We suspect someone killed Gu Mancang.

230
00:10:10,080 --> 00:10:10,880
So next,

231
00:10:11,120 --> 00:10:11,760
I need to ask you about

232
00:10:11,760 --> 00:10:14,240
Master Zheng Jinxian's schedule these past few days.

233
00:10:14,240 --> 00:10:15,680
Was there anything unusual?

234
00:10:15,680 --> 00:10:17,210
Please answer truthfully.

235
00:10:35,520 --> 00:10:36,580
What are you doing?

236
00:10:37,920 --> 00:10:38,400
I...

237
00:10:38,440 --> 00:10:40,440
I... I'm here to work.

238
00:10:41,160 --> 00:10:44,400
I heard the Zheng Residence is hiring.

239
00:10:45,720 --> 00:10:46,200
Sister,

240
00:10:46,640 --> 00:10:47,960
you really came to the right place.

241
00:10:47,960 --> 00:10:48,760
Our household

242
00:10:49,440 --> 00:10:51,900
really needs a sharp, capable maid like you.

243
00:10:54,080 --> 00:10:55,320
Brother,

244
00:10:55,800 --> 00:10:59,080
you must be highly valued in the Zheng household.

245
00:10:59,640 --> 00:11:02,080
Can you put in a good word for me

246
00:11:02,320 --> 00:11:03,450
and get me hired too?

247
00:11:03,760 --> 00:11:06,690
Actually, I've only been here for three or four days.

248
00:11:06,880 --> 00:11:07,400
But,

249
00:11:07,840 --> 00:11:09,240
there is no steward here.

250
00:11:09,720 --> 00:11:11,560
So everything in this mansion, up and down,

251
00:11:11,560 --> 00:11:12,840
inside and out,

252
00:11:13,040 --> 00:11:14,240
is taken care of by me.

253
00:11:14,600 --> 00:11:16,040
That must be tiring.

254
00:11:17,240 --> 00:11:18,840
What about the previous steward?

255
00:11:18,840 --> 00:11:19,700
Where did he go?

256
00:11:20,120 --> 00:11:21,200
How would I know?

257
00:11:21,920 --> 00:11:23,600
If you work for the Madam later,

258
00:11:23,600 --> 00:11:25,320
you have to be careful of the Master.

259
00:11:25,320 --> 00:11:25,800
He...

260
00:11:29,120 --> 00:11:29,680
He...

261
00:11:30,200 --> 00:11:31,360
is quite lecherous.

262
00:11:32,680 --> 00:11:33,880
Then what should I do?

263
00:11:34,280 --> 00:11:35,280
Then later,

264
00:11:35,520 --> 00:11:36,960
will I be in the East Wing

265
00:11:37,040 --> 00:11:38,700
serving the Master and Madam?

266
00:11:39,160 --> 00:11:39,600
No.

267
00:11:40,360 --> 00:11:42,090
The East Wing is always locked.

268
00:11:42,440 --> 00:11:43,280
The Master

269
00:11:43,520 --> 00:11:45,000
doesn't allow outsiders in there.

270
00:11:45,000 --> 00:11:45,480
The Madam

271
00:11:45,480 --> 00:11:47,410
is always resting in the West Wing.

272
00:11:49,440 --> 00:11:50,500
What are you doing?

273
00:11:50,960 --> 00:11:53,120
Didn't the Madam say there are rats in the kitchen?

274
00:11:53,120 --> 00:11:53,880
Did you buy the rat poison?

275
00:11:53,880 --> 00:11:54,640
I bought it.

276
00:11:55,360 --> 00:11:56,520
It's over at the gatehouse.

277
00:11:56,520 --> 00:11:57,920
I'll go spread it in a bit.

278
00:11:58,600 --> 00:12:00,730
Then Brother, I'm off to see the Madam.

279
00:12:00,880 --> 00:12:01,400
See you.

280
00:12:03,560 --> 00:12:05,280
What are you doing in our backyard?

281
00:12:05,280 --> 00:12:06,680
I'm going to the latrine.

282
00:12:06,800 --> 00:12:08,640
Are you the steward? Why do you care so much?

283
00:12:08,640 --> 00:12:09,120
I...

284
00:12:10,240 --> 00:12:12,100
What the hell are you laughing at?

285
00:12:12,720 --> 00:12:13,980
Hello, Director Song.

286
00:12:14,280 --> 00:12:16,440
I'm here representing Man Dali's family

287
00:12:16,440 --> 00:12:17,680
to bail him out.

288
00:12:18,200 --> 00:12:18,920
Bail?

289
00:12:19,760 --> 00:12:21,320
We haven't finished the interrogation.

290
00:12:21,320 --> 00:12:22,400
He can't be bailed out.

291
00:12:22,400 --> 00:12:23,280
You've interrogated him for two days.

292
00:12:23,280 --> 00:12:25,000
You haven't proven Man Dali is guilty.

293
00:12:25,000 --> 00:12:26,460
Why can't he be bailed out?

294
00:12:26,880 --> 00:12:28,000
According to the Criminal Procedure Law,

295
00:12:28,000 --> 00:12:29,330
Article 110 states that

296
00:12:29,840 --> 00:12:30,640
after detention,

297
00:12:30,640 --> 00:12:32,440
if further detention is deemed unnecessary,

298
00:12:32,440 --> 00:12:33,360
bail may be granted.

299
00:12:33,360 --> 00:12:35,440
Which law firm are you from?

300
00:12:35,880 --> 00:12:36,810
I'm not a lawyer.

301
00:12:37,720 --> 00:12:38,650
I am Luo Zhitang,

302
00:12:39,120 --> 00:12:41,040
a teacher at Fuyou School.

303
00:12:41,960 --> 00:12:44,480
So you're a teacher from Fuyou School.

304
00:12:44,800 --> 00:12:45,400
Yes.

305
00:12:47,760 --> 00:12:48,680
Vice Mayor Qian

306
00:12:49,320 --> 00:12:51,580
is the honorary principal of our school.

307
00:12:54,720 --> 00:12:56,880
Did you bring the bail money?

308
00:12:57,720 --> 00:12:58,580
Director Song,

309
00:12:58,800 --> 00:13:01,260
our rickshaw company will pay the full bail.

310
00:13:02,320 --> 00:13:02,960
Sansheng,

311
00:13:03,840 --> 00:13:05,360
take them to process the bail.

312
00:13:05,360 --> 00:13:05,880
Yes.

313
00:13:06,520 --> 00:13:06,960
Come.

314
00:13:07,280 --> 00:13:08,240
Follow me.

315
00:13:08,800 --> 00:13:11,260
That Ma Yanmei kept beating around the bush.

316
00:13:11,400 --> 00:13:13,200
I didn't get anything out of her.

317
00:13:13,680 --> 00:13:16,600
Looks like we have to wait for Zheng Jinxian to return.

318
00:13:16,600 --> 00:13:17,800
The servants at the Zheng residence

319
00:13:17,800 --> 00:13:19,400
only arrived three days ago.

320
00:13:19,760 --> 00:13:22,040
They don't know anything about the house.

321
00:13:22,040 --> 00:13:23,720
With Gu Mancang's monthly wage,

322
00:13:23,720 --> 00:13:25,040
he could afford opium,

323
00:13:25,680 --> 00:13:26,680
but how much did you

324
00:13:26,680 --> 00:13:28,400
pay the butler a month?

325
00:13:28,640 --> 00:13:30,640
We used to pay the butler

326
00:13:31,600 --> 00:13:33,330
thirty silver dollars a month.

327
00:13:33,600 --> 00:13:34,680
That's quite a lot.

328
00:13:35,400 --> 00:13:38,530
But the smell of smoke was concentrated in the East Wing.

329
00:13:43,680 --> 00:13:46,410
Why does the East Wing smell so strongly of smoke?

330
00:13:46,920 --> 00:13:49,440
A butler smoking in his master's room.

331
00:13:49,920 --> 00:13:51,320
That's very suspicious.

332
00:13:51,760 --> 00:13:54,290
Do you think Zheng Jinxian killed Gu Mancang,

333
00:13:54,760 --> 00:13:57,200
then framed Man Dali?

334
00:13:57,680 --> 00:13:59,200
He went out of town on purpose

335
00:13:59,200 --> 00:14:01,160
to create an alibi.

336
00:14:02,880 --> 00:14:04,400
But what I can be sure of is,

337
00:14:05,000 --> 00:14:06,520
there must have been another person that day

338
00:14:06,520 --> 00:14:08,120
who moved Gu Mancang's body.

339
00:14:08,800 --> 00:14:10,930
Right when that white smoke appeared.

340
00:14:12,680 --> 00:14:14,280
But how do you explain this?

341
00:14:14,880 --> 00:14:16,800
The photo of Zheng Jinxian that Ma Yanmei gave us

342
00:14:16,800 --> 00:14:19,200
doesn't look like the sketch or the corpse.

343
00:14:20,400 --> 00:14:22,730
Then who was the person who called the car?

344
00:14:23,200 --> 00:14:24,080
Well...

345
00:14:27,720 --> 00:14:28,520
We meet again.

346
00:14:29,560 --> 00:14:30,880
Just because you have four wheels.

347
00:14:30,880 --> 00:14:31,680
Not exactly.

348
00:14:31,960 --> 00:14:32,560
However,

349
00:14:32,720 --> 00:14:33,480
where are you going?

350
00:14:33,480 --> 00:14:35,740
I can give you a ride on these four wheels.

351
00:14:36,280 --> 00:14:37,400
No need. Thanks.

352
00:14:37,600 --> 00:14:39,860
Sure. Take us back to the Police Station.

353
00:14:41,320 --> 00:14:42,450
What a coincidence.

354
00:14:42,760 --> 00:14:44,890
We're going to the Police Station too.

355
00:14:45,120 --> 00:14:47,520
Aren't you Yang Moli's junior,

356
00:14:48,280 --> 00:14:49,000
Qiu Ya?

357
00:14:50,160 --> 00:14:51,640
We were both students at Deci Girls' High School.

358
00:14:51,640 --> 00:14:52,800
She was two grades ahead of me.

359
00:14:52,800 --> 00:14:54,480
She was quite the celebrity at school back then.

360
00:14:54,480 --> 00:14:55,160
Get in the car.

361
00:14:55,160 --> 00:14:55,560
Okay.

362
00:14:57,120 --> 00:14:58,200
You...

363
00:14:58,920 --> 00:14:59,760
You can go back now.

364
00:14:59,760 --> 00:15:01,440
We don't need you here anymore.

365
00:15:01,440 --> 00:15:03,080
Don't you dare cast me aside.

366
00:15:03,240 --> 00:15:05,240
Don't think you can shake me off. You're unbelievable.

367
00:15:05,240 --> 00:15:05,720
That's not cool.

368
00:15:05,720 --> 00:15:07,080
Why call yourself a donkey?

369
00:15:07,080 --> 00:15:09,410
I think "burning bridges" sounds better.

370
00:15:09,560 --> 00:15:10,560
You read too much.

371
00:15:11,800 --> 00:15:12,560
Show-off.

372
00:15:21,520 --> 00:15:22,120
Honey.

373
00:15:23,240 --> 00:15:24,680
Dali, you've suffered.

374
00:15:24,680 --> 00:15:25,880
It's okay. It's okay.

375
00:15:25,880 --> 00:15:26,440
It's all over now.

376
00:15:26,440 --> 00:15:27,400
This is Mr. Luo.

377
00:15:28,000 --> 00:15:29,640
Thanks to him for negotiating for you.

378
00:15:29,640 --> 00:15:30,700
Thank you, Mr. Luo.

379
00:15:31,200 --> 00:15:33,200
You are a great benefactor to me, Man Dali.

380
00:15:33,200 --> 00:15:34,130
Please, no need.

381
00:15:35,400 --> 00:15:37,260
I just know a little about the law.

382
00:15:37,800 --> 00:15:38,860
I didn't help much.

383
00:15:39,480 --> 00:15:40,540
Thank you, Mr. Luo.

384
00:15:40,680 --> 00:15:41,760
Thank you, ma'am.

385
00:15:41,840 --> 00:15:42,440
Thank you.

386
00:15:43,000 --> 00:15:43,760
Man Dali,

387
00:15:44,680 --> 00:15:46,680
don't go anywhere for now.

388
00:15:46,920 --> 00:15:49,960
We may summon you to assist in the investigation at any time.

389
00:15:49,960 --> 00:15:51,080
Yes, sir.

390
00:15:51,640 --> 00:15:53,240
According to the arraignment regulations,

391
00:15:53,240 --> 00:15:54,900
detainees and their families

392
00:15:55,360 --> 00:15:57,520
have the right to apply for a court hearing.

393
00:15:57,520 --> 00:15:59,200
This is to counter illegal detention

394
00:15:59,200 --> 00:16:01,120
and indirectly restrict indefinite interrogation.

395
00:16:01,120 --> 00:16:03,240
So, Director Song, please solve the case as soon as possible.

396
00:16:03,240 --> 00:16:04,720
Don't let these common folks

397
00:16:04,720 --> 00:16:06,180
live in constant anxiety.

398
00:16:10,200 --> 00:16:10,730
Let's go.

399
00:16:12,840 --> 00:16:13,370
Let's go.

400
00:16:16,240 --> 00:16:17,600
Who do you think you are?

401
00:16:17,760 --> 00:16:19,080
You're really pushing your luck.
